edu.harvard.data.io

Class JsonFileReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.harvard.data.io.JsonFileReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Iterable<Map<String,List<? extends DataTable>>>

    public class JsonFileReader
extends Object
implements Closeable, Iterable<Map<String,List<? extends DataTable>>>
    Stream class that parses an InputStream or local File containing JSON-formatted records. This class does not implement TableReader, since it is possible for one JSON record to produce many DataTable objects.

    This class is a wrapper around JsonFileIterator; see the documentation for that class for more details.

      • JsonFileReader

        public JsonFileReader(TableFormat format,
                      File file,
                      JsonDocumentParser parser)
               throws FileNotFoundException
        Create a new reader based on a local file.
        Parameters:
        format - the TableFormat that indicates how the data file is formatted.
        file - a File object that refers to the data file.
        parser - an implementation of the JsonDocumentParser interface that is able to convert a parsed JSON object into a set of all DataTable records contained within that JSON object.
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException - if the file parameter refers to a file that does not exist.

      • JsonFileReader

        public JsonFileReader(TableFormat format,
                      InputStream inStream,
                      JsonDocumentParser parser)
        Create a new reader based on an InputStream.
        Parameters:
        format - the TableFormat that indicates how the data file is formatted.
        inStream - an InputStream from which JSON-formatted records can be read. The stream will be closed when the close() method is called on this instance.
        parser - an implementation of the JsonDocumentParser interface that is able to convert a parsed JSON object into a set of all DataTable records contained within that JSON object.
